reviews: Wow! Our first trip to Paris was perfectly positioned thanks to our stay here in the Latin Quarter. Staff were helpful with recommendations, rooms were nicely furnished with amenities and BONUS! they have a small but terrific spa on site for free. We booked a triple room for our family of 3- a challenge to find rooms for more than 2 in the city. Rooms included an espresso machine, carafes of water and bathrobes which were appreciated during our busy stay. Excellent value for the location.

Great value for a central Paris location. A 5 minute walk from Luxembourg station on the RER Blue Line from Charles De Gaulle airport, access to the hotel is very straightforward. The hotel is modern inside, rooms are not huge but very comfortable with full and modern ensuite facilities. Highly recommended

We had a 19 hour layover for a connecting flight so time utilization was important. The hotel is less than a 10 minute walk to Notre Dame Cathedral. We were able to walk to the cathedral, the Louvre, Eiffel Tower and Arc de Triomphe. All in it's about 10 kilometers for this route but you can always use Uber if you're so inclined. We used Uber from the Champs Elysee to get back to the airport, the car picked us up in less than 4 minutes from when we placed our request.

We booked Grand Hotel Saint-Michel based on TripAdvisor reviews. The hotel is located in a great neighbourhood, close to restaurants and cafes and not far from major sights. The hotel is refurbished with lovely rooms that are quiet and comfortable with all amenities you need. Personnel is friendly and please ask reception for restaurant recommendations - they are great. Weâ€™ll be back here.

I canâ€™t possibly capture in words what a beautiful stay I had here. From the first contact confirming my reservation to the checkout was perfect! This was my first trip to Paris and they made it so special. I splurged on the panoramic view room with a balcony and it was huge! Gorgeous views of the Latin Quarter and the Pantheon! I ordered a half bottle of champagne to be waiting on my arrival but because of a misunderstood e-mail they didnâ€™t know I confirmed the request. They quickly remedied the situation and arranged (after hours) for a beautiful set-up! The bathroom was spacious with a multi head shower and rain shower. And of course the very European towel warmer! A separate water closet with a completely automatic bidet incorporated into the toilet, including a bum dryer. It was insanely fancy.
The staff was stellar. So friendly and accommodating. They even humored me when I wanted to speak French to them. I HIGHLY recommend this beautiful hotel. Itâ€™s in the perfect location on a quiet street in the middle of the Latin Quarter.

Excellent hotel , superb views from small balcony . Room clean , bathroom small but shower excellent ( rain shower / hand shower / jets ). Location Latin quarter and near to metro links . Great option away from the main sights , but close enough to walk to Notre Dame. Good options for breakfast close by. Hotel staff helpful .

I stayed 2 nights at Grand hotel Saint- Michel , it met my expectations ,
Positives:
- polite and helpful staff
- good location: 5 min walking distance from metro station
- fresh and delicious breakfast
- neat and clean room
Overally very good choice and recommendable.

Nice staff. Room clean, small size but very comfortable bed and pillows. Breakfast excellent choose. Even coffee was nice. Hair dryer would be better in bathroom, not in closet. Location is great, on the RER line from and to CDG airport. Recommend!

Expensive if you are staying in a single room. Not what I would term a 4 star hotel. No in room tea/coffee facilities, mini bar empty, hot food at breakfast was cold because apparently hot plate wasnâ€™t working properly. No bar. Bathroom recently decorated and pleasant. Room small which is not unusual in Paris. Baffled as to why no no coffee making facilities in a 4 star hotel. Reception staff pleasant. Pretty basic.

Staff are lovely at this hotel, but unfortunately our â€˜classicâ€™ room was very dark, depressing and had a horrible smell (Room 201) . Great location and nice breakfast, in a cleverly designed breakfast room. Canâ€™t understand why they havenâ€™t taken the same care with the rooms. I would return but would spend more money to have a brighter room. Corridors are brown and tired looking. A strange mixture of good and bad.

Was scheduled for a summer European tour and my passport renewal was delayed at the government agency. I had to cancel all flights and hotels! I booked ALL non refundable hotels and airlines and every company EXCEPT Grand Saint Michel gave me either full refunds or future credit and were flexible in accommodating me given my unfortunate circumstances. Grand Saint Michel was the only one that not only refused any sort of compensation but were hard to get in contact with and Marie the front desk personnel emailed me after a week of trying to get a hold of them letting me know itâ€™s their policy and was anything but hospitable. I tried informing them weeks in advance giving them ample time. These interactions are a representation of this place and with so many places in Paris to stay, I think you should be aware they will charge you over $1,000 even if you never set foot in their hotel. Terrible customer service

Friendly and responsive reception. Clean and comfortable, with coffee and amenities in the newly renovated rooms. Ir is conveniently located near the university, Notre Dame, good restaurants, book stores, museums. But it was really the nice, hard working staff that made this hotel earn 5 stars for me.

We thoroughly enjoyed our stay at this hotel. The rooms were small but the beds were comfortable and cozy. The daily breakfast is amazing, serving the best coffee, freash pastries and a variety of foods. Front desk staff were pleasant and so helpful.

This hotel was booked, directly with the hotel (I received confirmation and proceeded to book a car service that the hotel recommended) a month before we were to arrive. Then, 2 days before we arrived, I received an email saying they did not take Amex and that I needed to change my payment. Fine. But 2 (two) minutes later the hotel cancelled my booking saying they do not take Amex... but even in the cancellation booking, it clearly states that it does take Amex. Regardless, I would have been happy to give them another card for the nearly â‚¬1000 booking. The front desk said the booking was cancelled in the central office, and that they could not help me. Though I could go online and rebook a room.

This was less than 48 hours until we were to be in Paris. There was no offer to help, or to even rebook the room for me while I was on the phone. I also lost money in the car booking, which was only partially refundable.

In short, stay away from booking with this hotel. It is exceptionally expensive and a waste of time to try to rebook a hotel for 3 travellers in central Paris at such short notice.

After booking the hotel on line, when we arrived in front of the Hotel it was closed. It had been closed for two years. Luckily it wasnâ€™t the high tourist season and we managed to go down the street and book another hotel. We spent all morning trying to get reimbursed from Expedia.

We booked this hotel before Corona crisis arived in Europe - for a period where later the hotel was closed because of Corona. To support the hotel we agreed on to move our vacation here by one year without asking to get our money back what we had paid in advance - sure assumed that a stay would be possible this year.
Now after it is as well not possible to do a touristic trip to Paris this year the hotel is ignoring any contact! They keep the paid money completely even for breakfast!

It is extremely difficult to get help from the Grand Hotel Saint Michel. Have booked a room from 8 / 10-11 / 10-2020. There was no prepayment and free cancellation until June 6, 10-2020. On the 11/6, I canceled the hotel, and later that day the hotel spared a number of thousands in my account even though I had canceled. According to my bank, the money is to be withdrawn on December 26, ie in 3 days. I have tried to get help through booking.com, but Grand Hotel Saint Michel does not answer me nor booking.com. Seemed to be poor service and it leaves me in the uncertainty. Can't recommend this place, unfortunately.

First of all this hotel was so pretty and cute and quaint. They have the atmosphere down. I am American from SF and LA and Seattle. Me and my husband loved it here. They gave us a great room as total newbies and treated us with love and care. We are two huge men and we loved our room. The area is rich with food and drinks and people speech good enough English to take your order. We just absolutely loved it here 5 stars. We walked 1 hr to the Eiffel Tower and back and it was perfect. Donâ€™t take a Uber just walk. Safe streets and love people. I want to go back already and I havenâ€™t even left. Thanks for the best. We will book again.

Small hotel on a quiet side street but close to the Sorbonne, and many restaurants and bookshops. Outside itâ€™s a classic Parisian building, inside rooms are modern and stylishly comfortable. Nice amenities such as Clarins toiletries, spa on-site. Breakfast buffet was good but pricey. We prefer a la carte option or smaller traditional breakfast instead.
Would we stay at this lovely hotel again? Yes, most definitely.

We stayed at the hotel in July 2017 during a family trip. My husband and I were the first to arrive. Our room and bathroom were tiny but what view!!! Our family had total of four rooms and they were all different. Upon arrival I explained to the front desk that this trip is a dream come true for my 82 yr old mom and I wanted to make it extra special. They assign her a single room with a small balcony. It was perfect! She felt like a princess.

The breakfast was included and it was delicious. Also we couldn't ask for a better location. The neighborhood is great with transportation is nearby. I will definitely recommend this hotel and am looking forward to returning.

he hotel is modest-sized, sort of boutique. We stayed for 2 nights - a family of 5 in 1 family room and double room - 2 rooms Excellent communication some few days before arrival. Good location in the centre of Paris with shops and restaurants nearby, but not directly on the high street so it's more quiet. No parking though but street parking outside the hotel which cost 4 euros per hour. The check-in was smooth and the staff are polite and professional. The dining room was cosy and small, but the breakfast selection was small and extremely limited for picky eaters. The rooms were nice and the beds comfy - although double beds are singles put together, not unusual in hotels but it does not make for easy intimacy. The hotel has a sauna and gym in its base (where they also have the dining area). Overall it was lovely. Thanks all.

My overall rating of this property is somewhere between "Average" and "Very Good", but there is no such option. We had a mixed experience at GHSM that would be more accurately characterized as "Good" overall.

The staff could not have been any more accommodating... every concierge and housekeeper went out of their way to make us comfortable. The property itself was in need of attention. When I opened the door to our room, I was greeted by a number of carpet stains and an unpleasant cleaning product odor. Not small spots, but big patches of stain. Side chairs were covered with sticky vinyl material and the hotel information guide was tattered.

On the bright side, the bed was comfortable with clean linens and the shower had good pressure. I hid as much of the tattered, depressing stuff as possible in the closet and cracked the window. We avoided having our room cleaned during the rest of our stay.

We made it work, until we switched to our second hotel in a different part of town, but it was more work than I was interested in doing while on vacation. The photos online depict a cleaner, fresher more minimalist hotel with more upscale amenities than the one that we encountered in person.

I wish we could have stayed longer than one night - but alas we enjoyed the time we had here. We were able to visit lots of sites within walking distance and the location was perfect. Would recommend.

Nicely renovated boutique hotel in Latin Quarter, within walking distance to La Sorbonne, Pantheon, Luxembourg Gardens. We stayed in a Superior room which was one of their medium sized rooms with a king bed, that overlooked the street corner. Because of its closeness to La Sorbonne, night sounds were too obvious with street voices and vehicle sounds. The breakfast buffet offered a variety of selections. On one day, there were at 3 egg dishes; wish they offered all the times. Coffee, latte, or cafe au lair was very good. Waitress staff was excellent. Front office staff were attentive and made sure one was aware of possible demonstrations and metro closures or changes in availability. We didnâ€™t have time to use the spa (complimentary) or have afternoon tea or coffee & breakfast pastries.

Beautiful hotel. The staff was wonderful. Always greeted us with a smile, offered to assist with directions. They even informed us that it would cost more for a taxi to pick us up at the hotel than to walk one block to the taxi stand!
Breakfast staff very efficient. Coffee always ready when we sat down.
Located near the Sorbonne University. Easy walking to various sights.

Cozy hotel in the best area to stay in Paris, Saint Germain. If you stay or have stayed in this area you will understand why. Small rooms, but thatâ€™s pretty normal in this area. Would recommend to any friends and family.

As others have said, this hotel has a great location. The rooms and amenities were nothing special and not four star. Most hotel rooms in Paris are small and this was no exception. There are better places to stay.

The location of the hotel is great. Itâ€™s two blocks from the Sorbonne, within walking distance of some key sites (Louvre, Seine, Notre Dame), and in the middle of the energetic Latin Quarter. We had car trouble and Marie at the front desk was awesome - helped us get it fixed and was great. Quirky and fun rooms, and an oustanding breakfast offering.

Thank you so much Marie and Daniel. Iâ€™ve had the greatest hospitality ever in France.
I donâ€™t think I will ever want to stay in any other hotel next time when I visit. Hotel is so clean, great location, cool area, and homey.

The Best thing about this hotel was the LOCATION. The room was nice - small. Hair dryer was placed inside the closet which I found odd. Bathroom was updated and clean. House services were rude and not very friendly. Only two ladies at the front desk were so nice. They happen to be from Mexico and had such a pleasant and professional personality.

Very convenient location from the hotel with the Luxembourg Gardens just two blocks up the street and the Seine River and Notre-dame down several blocks from the hotel.
Shops and restaurants both ways from the hotel and across from the hotel is the Sorbonne.
Great staff from Lilian and the night clerk and others.
By the way they can provide transportation to the airport.

We stayed for two night. I booked a superior double. The room was not â€œsuperiorâ€ and we could hardly find a space to place our suitcases. It was room 105. The bath was broken. Most importantly - the noise. I could not sleep properly both nights because of the trucks right outside my window offloading stuff at 2-3 am and then later early in the morning. The breakfasts are very average. The words â€œgrandâ€ and â€œsuperiorâ€ are not applicable to this hotel and it is not four starts in my experience.

We stayed for four nights in the July 2019 heatwave, and found the hotel very welcoming and to a good standard. We had an inside room that only faced onto a very drab exterior wall, but the room itself was nice, with an en suite bath (which was really big!) with shower, and separate en suite toilet.

The Queen size bed was lovely and the air conditioning an absolute Godsend in the 42 degree heatwave! The list of channels supplied for the TV didn't correspond to those actually available on the TV itself, so there was nothing in English, but when in France...

The little pastries etc available downstairs through the PM were a nice touch, though we stayed clear of paying 15 euros per person per day for breakfast, so can't comment on that.

The hotel is right by the superb Luxembourg Palais and gardens, and has a number of handy shops within minutes walking distance; Monoprix supermarket, M&S food, McDonalds, etc, and is also only a short walk from the Odeon and Saint Michel Metro stations, Luxembourg station for the RER B train to Paris CDG airport (for which, the hotel happily printed us out our boarding passes from an email), and Notre Dame Cathedral.

Overall very happy, and we would use again if we ever return to Paris.

-- I have never seen a such a great hotel before... Everything was perfect and I don't know where to start.

  - The personnal and the service are very friendly and caring a lot.
  - For 15â‚¬ only, the breakfast was highly delicious, very cheap, quality food and there are a very large choice of tasties dishes.
  - Our room was pleasant and spacious, the bed very comfortable, nice view, beautiful decorations. The bathroom was clean and very well equiped with hair dryer, bathrobe, shampoo. Everything we needed !
  - The location of the hotel is perfect : close to the Pantheon, the Luxembourg Garden, Notre Dame, the Senate and lot of train stations, which facilitate the access to important places, like the Louvre, the Eiffel Tower or the Arch of Triumph !

I will come back again!

My wife and I have stayed in a few hotels in the area. This is definitely the worst out of the lot, not worth the price they charge. We had one of the best rooms with a lovely view. But constantly felt hotel were saving money at every opportunity. Not refilling toiletries, never leaving conditioner, having to be asked to replenish the complimentary water, checkout not having change so bill was rounded up (Not rounded down). Overall disappointed with our stay

Easily most friendly and delightful hotel staff I have dealt with in Paris but hotel rooms are average and facilities/Amenities are more three star than four. Saying that, the general star system for Parisian hotels seems to be on the inflated side.

Maybe my expectations were unrealistic but this is not a four star hotel. Itâ€™s fine. Nothing special. The staff is great. The amenities are great. The hotel is in a good location but the hotel itself isnâ€™t amazing. It worked though. The bathroom was nice.

I had a great stay here in May of 2018. Walking distance to several bucket list sites. The main concierge was very helpful in booking nearby attractions; she also helped me navigate the various transportation options - of which there are many! The room was comfortable and clean. The Chinese restaurant across the street is AMAZING!! Overall great stay.

This is my new favorite affordable hotel in Paris. It's right by the Sorbonne, about a 15-minute walk to Notre Dame. There are some awesome bookstores nearby and plenty of other shopping and eating options. Luxembourg Gardens is around the corner. And it's right by the RER B train line, so it's a straight shot back to the Charles de Gaulle airport. I had a room on the 6th floor with just an amazing view. Highly recommended.

We stayed at the Grand Hotel Saint Michel for 3 nights. We stayed in the superior room, which had a balcony and a magnificent view. The hotel is perfectly located with central access to metros, cafes, and shops. Our stay was absolutely wonderful- the hotel was spotless, and we received the most amazing service from the front desk- in regards to directions, or recommendations of where to eat- they were always super cheerful and were more than eager to help. Our trip consisted mostly travelling during the day, so we mostly just returned to the hotel late at night- but it was super comforting to know that we were returning to such a great hotel and great room. We highly recommend anyone who would like to stay in a hotel with an amazing location and amazing service to stay at the Grand Hotel Saint Michel. We definitely will be returning there for our next stay in Paris.

Great hotel in the Latin quarter. Walking distance to a lot of bars and restaurants.
Wonderful staff very helpful and all spoke wonderful English, because our French was not so good. The room was small but wonderfully appointed and immaculately clean. Don't miss the spa room. And there is a lovely breakfast area downstairs. I love how they changed all the flowers every few days.

We really enjoyed our stay here. The location is excellent and the staff really go out of their way to be helpful. An amazing perk is the Turkish bath (they call it a "Hamam Sauna"). It's a private suite of rooms with a steam room, high end electric massage chair, and hydro massage bed. We booked it for 2 hours and felt completely refreshed, having been exhausted from too much walking. Amazing!

the hotel is located in a very good place in the latin qoarter - you can just walk to many places from there.
the service was unique - always patient and wellcoming, we recieved a lot of information ang good recomendations. lilian was just great
the hotel has a hamam - water bed massage; steam room, sofa massage. after along day of walking its the best way to relax
the hottel offers coffee ant tea in the noon and watter all day long/
dont miss it

Fantastic stay. The service is outstanding, the rooms are beautiful and the location is so central, yet in a quiet street. Breakfast is varied, hot and cold options with quality food and fresh orange juice. I also really liked the free 1h per day hammam/relaxation seat/hydro jet bed included in the room fee. This hotel is now my favourite one in Paris!

Stayed three nights in February. Excellent location in the 6th/St Germain. Walkable to great sights and restaurants. Very lively area near the Sorbonne so there can be some noise outside late night. Didnâ€™t bother us too much. Room was small but thatâ€™s Paris. Bathroom was a perfect size though. Canâ€™t say enough about the staff. Front desk spoke English very well and were extremely accommodating. Helpful with directions and recommendations. Had breakfast one morning and it was simple but nice. Coffee, juice, pastries, some eggs. All in all a great choice for the money!

This hotel was a good little base for our weekend stay in Paris. We arrived on the Friday and was able to check into a room a little earlier. Were given a room on the 6th floor which we could see the pantheon from the window.
Room was fine for our stay, clean, enough space for what we needed it for.
Elemis toiletries in the bathroom.
Thankful for the safe in the room which was easy to use.
Very welcoming staff who were also very helpful with recommendations.
Tea time offered at the hotel free of charge 2-7pm was welcomed. However I think an easy change could be to provide tea and coffee making facilities in the rooms, this was something that I did miss.

The hotel is pretty central to many places, notre damn around a 10 minute walk. We didnâ€™t eat at the hotel, we chose to visit the local bakery near moubert metro.
From gare du nord itâ€™s around 4 stops to Luxembourg metro station on I believe the B train (RER). Then a 5 minute walk to the hotel.
We didnâ€™t bother with weekend books or tickets for the trains as we chose to walk to most places.
We were able to store our luggage on our last day whilst we finished exploring before catching our Eurostar home.

We did visit the â€˜spaâ€™ at the hotel for an hour- the massage chair and bed are amazing!

A good little hotel that I would recommend, thank you.

This hotel is in a great location for a sightseeing trip to Paris - 5mins walk from Luxembourg & 10 min walk from St Michel metro stations, both on direct RER line from CDG airport. Very clean & comfortable rooms, but would have liked tea/coffee making facility in room. Friendly and helpful staff. Would certainly stay here again on any future trip to Paris.

If I was staying here only for accomodation they would get four stars. Unfortunately I am here for the meetings and they are just not made for it. The room I slept was OK, size not big but managable. Bathroom brand new but room furniture is getting old. Breakfast is fine but not extraordinary.

Nice hotel conveniently located in Quartier Latin. Only a 5 minute walk from RER/ metro station Luxembourg, with direct trains to/from CDG airport. It is also within walking distance from Notre Dame, Pont Neuf and the Marais- area. It took us about 30 mins to walk to Louvre.
We had a nice, clean and OK sized room for 3 persons. Functional wi-fi in the room. The check- in staff and breakfast staff were helpful, but the receptionist on duty saturday night refused to sell us a bottle of water! A bit strange, but all in all the staff we met was polite and smiling!
The breakfast is really good, and is served until 11.00 am during weekends!
Highly recommended for a reasonably priced and very nice located hotel in Paris!

The breakfast was very good and the restaurant was quaint. Plenty of choice and staff were friendly and helpful there. For check in and checkout the reception staff were very helpful and polite. We were particularly lucky with the excellent restaurant recommendations we were given for both of our evening meals. Our room was well-presented and clean. The bed was very comfortable. There was no shower door so the bathroom floor got very wet every time we showered. In addition, because the exterior Christmas lights were lit from cables inside the bedrooms the bathroom appeared a little dangerous with a wet floor and electric cables. Nevertheless, the hotelâ€™s Christmas decorations looked lovely. We had an excellent stay and the staff were welcoming and helpful. The location was very good too - only a short walk to nearby shops and restaurants yet the street was peaceful at night. Iâ€™d happily recommend this hotel.

In short: A very generous upgrade meant that our lodgings became one of the highlights of our short city break. And that's saying something for a city as beautifully engaging and attraction-tastic as Paris.

The long story: It's actually somewhat difficult for me to properly review the GHSM, because although we stayed there for three nights, we didn't actually stay there... Upon check-in, Reception advised of a "problem" with our room: not exactly sure what this meant, but ultimately it did not matter in the slightest as they offered us an upgrade to an off-site apartment that's normally used for long-stay bookings that require self-contained facilities. As it transpired, we found ourselves in a glorious 2-bed, second-floor apartment overlooking the Pantheon, living the life of the bourgeoisie.

Therefore, it's hard for me to do justice to a review of the main hotel location. Suffice to say that our experiences with the front-of-house staff were universally positive; they were always polite, friendly, professional, and helpful. For the record, the hotel is located on a small and relatively quiet street in the Sorbonne area, so it's somewhat bohemian with plenty of students, student-orientated shops, but also quite a few quality hotels and restaurants/cafes; the location is safe and pleasant.

Furthermore, it's an easy walk to local attractions such as the Pantheon, the Luxembourg Gardens and its Museum (currently hosting a fantastic Alfonse Mucha exhibition), the Musee Curie, and only 800m to Notre Dame and the Seine. There is a nearby transit station (the RER B line) but, to be honest, you're always better to try to walk an old-world city like Paris; it's the only true way to get the feel and the most out of your visit. I'd also recommend one of the river transit services such a Batobus; another great way to see more while getting around between the major attractions.

The acid test (that is, would I return): Certainly, and without hesitation.

We stayed for 5 nights in late October. The room was exactly as expected. It was clean, the linens and bed were excellent and the location worked for us.
The fridge is teeny and filled with water, juice...there is a charge for these items. There is a charge sheet in the desk blotter listing the item costs. We simply moved the bottles outside the fridge to make room for our beer and wine. Before we left, we placed the bottles back in the fridge, no issues there.

The staff are excellent and very helpful always saying good morning and wishing you a good day and welcoming you back when you return. It's a nice personal touch.
We enjoyed the tea time on a few occasions when we need a caffeine jolt in the afternoon.

We tried the steam room one afternoon. It was clean, and intimate. A good experience.

Tips:
The closet has minimal hangers, pack extra hangers if you need to hang more than 5 things.
This hotel does not supply washcloths (face cloths). Bring your own if you need.
Controls for heat/AC are in the room but the actual control is with the front desk. A quick call will get the temperatures adjusted for you.
The hotel can make arrangements for a private driver if you need. We coordinated airport transport through the hotel and had no issues.
If your room is facing the street it can get a bit loud in the morning (garbage collection). We brought ear plugs anticipating the noise.

I would recommend this hotel to family and friends.

Easy to access through RER B from Paris airports. Luxembourg Gardens is 2 blocks away. Easy metro and bus access to everywhere in Paris. This hotel is hard to beat for the good rate it offers.....highly recommended....

Was in Paris for business meetings and needed somewhere convenient to stay, Grand Hotel Saint Michel was a good choice, located conveniently near the metro to CDG airport, the Sorbonne and central Paris, easy to get around, by metro, uber or taxi, the room was comfortable, location was quiet and the staff were friendly and helpful

We had a pleasant stay at this hotel during the first week of September. the hotel was conveniently located near various train and bus stations and had a bunch of restaurants and bars within walking distance. the room was pretty small but i guess its like all paris hotel rooms, with just enough space for 2 people. bathroom was very small, but shower did not have a curtain or a full glass door because of which the water fell outside of the shower area near the door onto the carpet of the bedroom. the air conditioning was pretty wonky too, we couldnt control it directly from our room and had to tell the front desk everytime to turn it on and off. it was very inconvenient especially as we didnt have temperature control and it was freezing with their settings. there was a spa and tea area available but we did not end up using either of them. people at the front desk were friendly and helpful. All in all, a very average place to stay 3-4 nights.

Very nice, stylish and clean hotel in a great location. The room may seem small but is actually quite a good size for a central Paris hotel. Lots of restaurants and shops nearby and a few of the historical monuments too. Easy access to multiple metro stations. We found the service to be great, all the ladies at reception were very helpful with queries and polite. The steam room was a bonus, nice little area well maintained. The complimentary afternoon tea downstairs is a good concept although not to provide tea bags etc in the room was a slight negative. Would definitely stay here again, for me this is the best hotel I have stayed in Paris when everything is factored in. The price was good too!

I stayed at the hotel for a short night. The people at reception at check in as well as check out were very nice, helpful and hospitable.
The room was small, but that is what you should expect in this hotel and in the nearby hotels. The room was nicely decorated and contained all the usual amenities.The area of Saint-Michel is good for restaurants, with lots of young people around.

We stayed here for seven nights recently. This hotel is a gem. It is one block from Blvd. Saint Michel, two metro stations a short walk away, close to the Pantheon and Luxembourg Gardens. Lots of restaurants close by with all types of cuisine.
The staff here are excellent. Starting with Sylvio who handled all my reservation questions promptly by email. The front desk staff of Clotilde, Lilian and Marie only to glad to help with any questions regarding local travel. Marie was kind enough to print our boarding passes for our return flight.
The room on the 4th floor faced out to the street. It was sound proof, we did not even hear the people in the next room, no plumbing noise, even the air conditioning was whisper quiet.
The bed and pillows were firm yet comfortable.
The bathroom was very nice and the combination tub/shower had a good size water shield.
We opted for the buffet breakfast to save time in the morning.
It featured the usual hot and cold items, scrambled eggs, sausage and bacon, a selection of cold cuts, fruit salad, assorted cereals, yogurt and pastries.
This is a great hotel in a great neighborhood. You wonâ€™t be disappointed.

Beautiful hotel in Latin district, close to Pantheon, great dining choices, and short walk to Notre Dame. The rooms are very clean, quiet and just lovely. The staff here is extremely attentive, helpful and pleasant. We will stay here again for sure! Thank you for making our Paris stay lovely.

As always, the Grand Hotel Saint-Michel was fantastic.

Pros: exceptionally helpful staff (particularly Clotilde and Lilianne); well-appointed rooms with relatively comfortable dimensions given its Europe; Hermes bath products; balcony was lovely, had patio furniture and had a spectacular view of the skyline; linens and bed were comfortable; excellent assistance booking tours and with directions, contacting taxis, and arranging reservations.

Cons: hotel is located next to a day care and down the street from a popular student bar, so a bit noisy at night and busy during the week (not, in my view, really an actual con, merely a note).

DEFINITELY staying there again.

We were spending 5 nights at this lovely hotel. Convenient location- just a few min walk from the Metro station, lots of restaurants, shops, supermarkets...everything!
The room itself is pretty tiny but we found it very comfortable, the bath was big enough (almost the same size as the room itself).
Everything was very clean, towels were replaced on a daily basis, soap and shampoo were generously given every day, the bed was comfortable, tlbed linen were clean. the stuff was friendly, there is a Hamam area for free!!! I really did not expected such a good experience and was afraid to meet overrated hotel. I will absolutely come back in the future.

We very much enjoyed our stay. The staff was particularly helpful and cheerful. They went out of their way to make us feel welcome and were very attentive. We like the location. It was easy to use the bus and train system from the hotel. The rooms are clean but very small, which I understand is common in Paris. The breakfast we extremely good!

Loved our stay at Grand Hotel Saint-Michel! It was a great location. The front desk was helpful with everything we needed. We loved their Tea time and couldn't have been happier. Room was a little small but worked out ok. All kinds of restaurants close by. We ate breakfast there and it was also very good.

Located in the Quartier Latin, but on a quiet side street and not right in the midst of the hustle and bustle. Easy access to metro.

Room is compact but as expected for a single room. Well maintained. Bathroom is top notch, small. Bed is extremely comfortable. Nice windows that open.

I didnâ€™t find a restaurant in the area that didnâ€™t suffer from tourist-syndrome (in other words, they cater to tourists and not to locals, hence the quality is lacking). However, Breakfast at the hotel is very reasonably priced, on par with what is around, and the food is very good, fresh with many choices.

Tea time in the lobby from 2-7 - complimentary coffee, tea, pastries. Nice touch.

Staff are pleasant and helpful and know enough English to get by.

Great value for the price.

I wouldnâ€™t change a thing.

I took my mom to Paris to celebrate her birthday. The hotel was beautiful, centrally located (not too close to hustle and bustle but still plenty to do within walking distance). The breakfast was good and the staff was super friendly, especially Maria who gave us a friendly welcome to cafÃ© and croissants upon arrival and even let us check into our room early! Really liked the private workout room with sauna, too!

The hotel was very nice. It was a very short walk from the RER train from the airport. The lady at reception was very nice and spoke English. She also was able to answer questions and give suggestions each day. The room was small but standard for Europe hotel rooms. The bathroom was large and clean. We were able to open the room windows for fresh air and to take some pictures. The twin beds were comfortable and I slept soundly each night. I would stay here again.

Great location - in a quiet street next to the pretty boulevard st michel. Really close to subway or you can also easily walk to the seine & notre dame and start your day in Paris. Lots of great restaurants nearby and the parc de Luxembourg.

But what makes this hotel really worth it is the exellent service & staff. Very helpfull and welcoming! We arrived very early but were greeted with an espresso and a smile. They also gave a great recommendation to have dinner and made the reservations for us.

The room is nice, clean, modern bathroom, great bed. The balcony is GREAT, nice little place to chill and look over the rooftops of Paris.

I have been to Paris for about 8 times allready and this was definetly the best experience. Great service for a good price. If we go back to Paris we will definetly stay here again!

I absolutely loved this quiet little hotel. Clean, convenient, gracious and friendly staff, within walking distance to most major attractions (or use Luxembourg metro). Fantastic breakfasts and numerous restaurants and bistros nearby. We stayed by happenstance - next time it will be by choice! Thanks to Marie and Daniel who went above and beyond. Fantastic!

We had the pleasure to stay here on our trip to Paris. Great little hotel. We were expecting it to be tiny but to our surprise more than enough room for a family.
Great location, very close to Notre Dame and local dining. Make sure you spend a few hrs enjoying a drink on the sidewalk cafe

A small hotel in a key position very close to Sorbonne, Pantheon, Quartier Latin and a short walk from NÃ´tre Dame and Saint Germain des Pres. Lots of good shops and restaurants around the corner. Amazing staff that are so friendly and welcoming and keen to assist you and cater to your every need. Complimentary refreshments and snacks in the lobby are a nice gesture. Breakfast is delicious and rich and in a nice cozy setting. Rooms are very small but clean, relatively practical and have all the basic amenities.

Excellent hotel with the friendliest staff around. Spent five nights here and enjoyed it greatly. Convenient location. Walking distance to many places to eat, site seeing and public transportation. Breakfast was pricey but delicious.

The hotel is well situated. It is very convient to the Metro and many attractions. The staff was extremely friendly and helpful. The rooms were very clean and comfortable. The complementary tea in the reception area was lovely and they had a nice variety of food at the breakfast buffet. The wifi connection was great! Overall, a great experience!

Small boutique style hotel in university area - quiet street but a lot of restaurant options nearby. Close to Notre Dame, Louvre, Pantheon, Gardens, grocery, banks, tea shops, bakeries - excellent location and value for the money. Rooms are small, clean - breakfast available. The staff goes above and beyond - very genuine and friendly. Honestly, some of the nicest staff I have ever encountered. My sons and I loved the area - perfect for our stay. So glad I found this place!

Very friendly staff who go out of the way to make your stay comfortable. It was nice they had a complementary sauna room and massage chair. Not to forget they provide you with the best toileteries.
Rooms were small but I guess that's expected in big city like Paris.

This hotel is located in a great area convenient to many attractions and very safe. Beds are comfortable and staff are very friendly and accommodating. Decor is a bit tacky and the hotel is in need of some freshening up.
I would stay again, but 4-star is not appropriate for this hotel.

Typical small Parisian hotel in Sorbonne district. Exceptionally helpful receptions staff. Clean and cosy room with bath tub. Memorable touches such as free serving of fruit and macarons in bedroom and free afternoon tea and cake in reception. Quality breakfast.
Excellent location in quiet street close to Luxembourg gardens and easy stroll to centre.

The hotel location was perfect, not too busy. The staff were wonderful, friendly and extremely helpful!

The whole place is immaculately clean including the rooms, a bit small but adequate. There was nespresso machine, which was great. There was a very nice afternoon tea provided every day.

Would recommend!
Thank you to all the staff at the hotel, definitely stay there again.

Perfect location! The hotel is in the Latin Quarter, and close to the metro. When we arrived the hotel was fully booked, we ended up on the first floor, which was a bonus for us. Our room was roomy, and clean, and included an espresso machine. The staff were very helpful, especially Silvio. We will definitely choose this hotel on our next visit to Paris!

The hotel was clean and pretty but the rooms very tiny. We could barely fit all our luggage in it. The staff were lovely and very helpful. Good breakfast and a good spot in the city - not too busy but still a nice area to walk around.

The kindness, friendliness and professionalism of Ms. Clotilde, and of the entire staff at Grand Hotel St Michel, made our stay perfect. Clotilde went above and beyond to help us. The hotel was immaculately clean, and a delightful afternoon tea was provided every day. Ideal for families, seniors and honeymooners, this hotel will make your Paris stay memorable.

The hotel is about 2 mins walk from the station (only 3 stops from gare du nord where Eurostar stops) and has plenty of ice cream parlours and restaurants nearby.
The staff here were very friendly and welcoming, service with a smile.
The hotel is chic and pretty, room were nice, clean and had good WiFi connection. Also every afternoon they have tea, coffee and pastry available in the lobby - nice touch! The breakfast selection was good and they made gooood cappuccino :)
All the landmarks were nearby such as pantheon, Notre Dame cathedral and Louvre, while the rest you can easily get by the subway (eg Eiffel Tower).
We will definitely stay here again when we next visit Paris! Merci!

A fun modern hotel with a helpful and welcoming staff. Nice rooms with all you need. Well located a short walk from Luxembourg gardens and Notre Dame. Very easy to get to from airport. Itâ€™s just a few minutes from RER station.

We stayed at this cute and chic Hotel and we were travelling with my 2 year old, so we stayed in one of the suites, where there was an extra bed and it worked out perfect for us. The hotel folks - Clotilde and team were super friendly at the front desk always, they were excellent about meeting all our requests for the room, providing us directions and what public transport to take to all the touristy sites. Since we would be out all day - were sad to miss the lovely tea time they have at the Hotel in the afternoons. Loved the location - was only 12 minute walk from Notre-Dame and close by Metro, and so many local delicious places to eat at near by, local artisan stalls with food & handicrafts down the road and countless high end and mid range stores to shop around. Absolutely fantastic! Was really the ideal place for us as a family to stay at. Merci Beaucoup to all for your wonderful hospitality at the Hotel again!

Rooms are small, BUT larger than I expected or Paris. A lot of folks post about small rooms in their review, but this is totally normal for a city like Paris. Hotel is centrally located and easy to take public transport or walk to other parts of town. There's a Monoprix and Marks and Spencer nearby making it easy to grab a snack or bottle of watter. The Hammam spa wasn't working during our stay. The tea/water/snacks available during the afternoon were a nice touch. my only complaint would be the humidity in the rooms. Unfortunately, all my clothes came home with a mildew-like smell that have required a great number of washes to remove.

My husband and 17 year old daughter and I arrived on April 19th to visit my son who is studying in Paris. We stayed until April 23rd. Then visited London.
The staff was very nice and spoke English! The room was clean and while it was small (donâ€™t bring large pieces of luggage ) the three of us were very comfortable!
The bed was amazing! Our room had a separate room just for the toilet which made showering and doing hair and makeup easier!
Donâ€™t hesitate to stay here! Here are some photos of the lobby!

We spent four night in this very lovely hotel. The location was perfect for sightseeing, local restaurants, and a good nights sleep. The staff were friendly and welcoming and our room was comfortable and clean. If you are looking for updated accommodations in a nice neighborhood then you should strongly consider Grand Hotel Saint Michael! You will not be disappointed.

Second visit to to this wonderful hotel. Tucked beneath the shadows of the Pantheon and adjacent to the Luxembourg Gardens in the Latin Quarter, what makes hotel the true gem that it is are the people. Starting with the General Manager Marie, not only is she genuinely interested in the quality of your stay, but she imparts this concept onto her staff. Lilian and Annalisa at reception are so pleasant and will go out of their way to tend to your needs. Even the housekeepers are friendly and will speak to you, though you better do better with your French than I did. The breakfast here is outstanding- really good, fresh food - eggs, huge assortment of cheese, croissants, fruit, yogurt- everything. My favorite this trip was Clotilde. Not only does her warm smile and sparkling eyes melt your heart, as you enter the hotel like me with a few phrases in French memorized, and then you fumble them all, she will say in perfect English â€œOh you speak perfect Frenchâ€. God love her!

Of note, this hotel is 10 minute walk to Norte Dame, 20 to Bastille, short Uber to the Montparnasse Tower for Parisâ€™ best view of the Eiffel Tower- go after dark. Plenty of nice places to eat and an I cream shop just steps around the corner.

Great location. Room is small like in Tokyo hotels, but more stlyish. Staff are very friendly and helpful. Breakfast is good compared to European norm. My wife love this hotel. Close to RER. Only few minutes walk.

Stayed here for 10 nights and there is absolutely nothing bad I can say about this hotel. The staff were very friendly and helpful and the location canâ€™t be better. Youâ€™re only about a five minutes walk away from Notre-Dame and many metro stations. Our room came with a free breakfast that was very good. The only thing that could have been a little better was the bed, which was a little firm for my taste.

Very good hotel. The rooms are small like every hotel in Paris but they are very well decorated.
The location is awesome, close to Boulevard Saint Michel, between the Pantheon and Sorbonne. Many many restaurants, bars and pubs close to the hotel.
The staff is friendly and they speak many languages (portuguese, spanish, english..).
Breakfast is ok, but the evening complimentary coffee is a plus.

The hotel is small but recently updated and very modern. The staff is super friendly and helpful. There is no restaurant but breakfast buffet is varied and plentiful and includes fresh squeezed orange and grapefruit juice.

Let's be honest. GHSM is no boutique hotel, and the room I had could do with some TLC, but what this property lacks in freshness of decor, it more than makes up in excellent location and cleaniness.
It's a stone throw away from Notre Dame and Latin quarter, literally next door to the Sorbonne. And staff are so professional and friendly. I really enjoyed my stay.

We arrived first at CDG Airport got the RER B train to Luxembourg Train Station. 10.60 Euros per person by the way. Hotel is about five minutes walk down the road easy to find just of Rue Cujas. Staff are excellent, welcoming, easy to deal with. Lobby is welcoming. Rooms are what you expect from a city, small but adequate. Clean, Bed sheets were good, pillows etc. Mini-Bar, safety deposit box, great Hermes Shower gel. Breakfast is continental, meats, cheeses, eggs, cereal, bread, Nutella. City is a bit noisy so you could be woken up by the busy people. Great Location for the sights, restaurants, bars, super markets, shops, Mcdonalds, Burger King, Loads to keep you busy. If I were to return to Paris, I would put this hotel at the top of a list for price, comfort, location, safety and the overall good factor.

We booked a superior twin room and it was very comfortable but a bit small. Lots of mirrors everywhere and the room was red and black. The beds were very comfy and the tv was huge. The mini bar only stocked soft drinks, which was a pity. The bathroom was lovely, with lots of toiletries including the ubiquitous sewing kit. The breakfasts were great, with a good selection of hot and cold food and every afternoon in the lobby, they provided tea, coffee and pasties for the guests. It is only e few minutes from Luxembourg Rer, which made our trip from Gard du Nord to our hotel very easy as it is only 3 stops. Not terribly atmospheric but very clean and shiny.

Definitely worth booking! I stayed here for 2 nights with 2 friends and loved it. Our room was not only larger than expected (by European standards) but comfortable & chic. The bathroom was spacious and great water pressure. We had an interior view and even that was lovely, and noiseless. It's located down the street from the Luxembourg Garden and maybe 10 min walk from metros, which is worth it to take in the city and all the cafes. It is also located 3 blocks away from a direct train line to CDG airport - 41 min total!

The hotel offers complimentary tea & pastries between 3pm-8pm. Welcoming at all times of day and night. My flight was at 6pm and they held my luggage so I could walk around worry-free.

This is a nice hotel, it has excellent staff and great facilities. However, the dÃ©cor and design is quite something to behold. From the Faux Snake-Skin wallpaper to the bright coloured rooms, this is truly not for the person who loves their bulk standard beige hotels. However, if you want something comfortable, different and in a great location, then you've just found it.

Nice small boutique type hotel close to Jardin Luxembourg. Quiet street. Walking distance to the park, Notre Dame, RER station, Sorbonne etc.
Good restaurants near by.
Friendly and helpful staff and they also speak english.
We like to stay at this hotel every time when in Paris.
Excercise room too small. It is filled up with 3 cardio equipment and one massage chair. No space foor stretching out or doing any kind of excercise on the carpet/floor . Remove some of the big equipment and replace them with free weights

Stayed with my fiancÃ©e for 2 nights . 10 min max walk from
Metro and only three stops away from gare du nord.
Staff are excellent, friendly and canâ€™t do enough for you. We were offered a Cup of tea of coffee on arrival then went to the room . Very clean room and comfortable bed. The rooms are a bit small but you expect that in a big city . And youâ€™re not likely to be spending too long in it when in Paris.
Itâ€™s a ten minute walk to notre dame. We didnâ€™t use the metre for the three days apart from arriving and going. Walked everywhere taking in the beautiful surroundings.
One thing Iâ€™d recommend is that they put tea and coffee making facilities in the rooms, but you can get them in reception anytime.
Thereâ€™s a good choice for breakfast too, nice room downstairs.
Would go again here .

This was a return visit after two years, and the desk staff convincingly remembered me (Clotilde in particular). I asked for the same room that my wife and had I occupied and sure enough little had changed: the staff went out of their way to be welcoming and to provide concierge service. All were either fluent in English or at least capable, and did their best to accommodate my rudimentary French. Requested service was prompt and courteous. The room was tiny by American standards, in the usual way of French hotels, but everything was new-looking, completely clean, even elegant in a modern Euro sort of way. But practice walking sideways. The balconies are also very small, but have room enough to sit. Breakfast was comprehensive, from yogurt and honey to pastries and croissants, to charcuterie and a delicious selection of whole cheeses that you cut yourself. The hot dishes looked fine, but I didn't feel the need to try them. The location, next to the Sorbonne, a full block from bustling rue St.Michel on a one way street going toward rue St.Michel, so traffic noise is seldom a problem. The neighborhood is filled with university students and kindergartners, a few minutes walk from one of the Major RER and Metro lines, three short blocks from the Luxembourg garden, and an easy downhill walk to Notre Dame: all in all fantastic location.

We loved this hotel. We were on a family vacation - a group of 7 - to Italy but decided to start with a weekend in Paris. This hotel was in an excellent neighborhood with great restaurants nearby.

The hotel is very modern -chic would be the right word. The lobby is small and the rooms are tiny but perfectly clean and just enough space for what you need. For heavens sake you are in Paris. Get out and explore!! Some rooms have very quaint Juliet balconies.

The staff is amazing. Very friendly and helpful. We loved the breakfast. I can't wait to go back.

We want to remark the good vibes with the hotel staff, really nice people all of them Galicia, Clotilde, I cannot remember the name of the other colleges, but thanks to everyone.
We found the hotel really nice, and we loved the breakfast!
We really recommend it!
